// connector.proto — Mode-C plugin daemon protocol (#438).
//
// Generic source-connector RPC schema used by kapi to dispatch
// push/pull/status/list against a plugin running as a Mode-C daemon
// (long-lived subprocess speaking gRPC over a local Unix socket).
//
// Lives in the framework module so cli/ and kapi/ can dial daemons
// without depending on any specific plugin (e.g., bowrain). Each Mode-C
// plugin implementing source connectors serves both services on its
// daemon socket; the kapi-side DaemonPool acquires the gRPC connection
// and a plugin-supplied dispatcher issues the RPC.

